This paper focuses on evaluating the performance of a desynchronization algorithm for wireless sensor networks, which falls under the category of networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impacts of period length and channel utilization fairness, which are related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and control systems (cs.SY). The simulation and experimentation aspects of the paper may also fall under the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG).
